                                        <h1>ShriGo Terms & Conditions</h1>
                                        <div class="effective-date">Effective Date: 03May2026</div>

                                        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
                                        <p>ShriGo is a platform connecting drivers and passengers for ride-sharing services. By using our platform, you agree to these Terms & Conditions and Privacy Policy.</p>

                                        <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Driver/Passenger  must be at least 18 years old</li>
                                            <li>Driver/Passenger must provide accurate and complete information during registration.</li>
                                            <li>ShriGo can suspend accounts for false information</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    <hr />
                                        <h2>3. Driver Terms</h2>

                                        <h3>3.1 Registration</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <h5>Drivers must:</h5>
                                        <li>Register on ShriGo and provide valid details </li>
                                            <ul style="padding-left:40px">
                                                <h5>Upload required documents:</h5>  
                                            <li>Driver Aadhaar</li>
                                            <li>RC</li> 
                                            <li>Vehicle Insurance</li>
                                            <li>Vehicle Number</li>
                                            <li>Vehicle Tax license</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>3.2 Responsibilities</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Ensure passenger safety</li>
                                            <li>Follow traffic laws</li>
                                            <li>No drunk driving</li>
                                            <li>Maintain professional behavior</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>3.3 Ride Management</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Drivers must upload rides</li>
                                            <li>Drivers are responsible to complete ride, once a booking is confirmed</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>3.4 Pricing</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Drivers set pricing per trip or per passenger</li>
                                            <li>ShriGo will charge Drivers a monthly subscription</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>3.5 Cancellation</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>No cancellations after booking</li>
                                            <li>Alternate driver must be arranged if needed</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>3.6 Liability</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Drivers and insurance are responsible for accidents or incidents</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    <hr />
                                        <h2>4. Passenger Terms</h2>

                                        <h3>4.1 Booking</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Passengers book rides via the platform</li>
                                            <li>Must pay agreed fare at the time of booking</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>4.2 Responsibilities</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Be on time at pickup</li>
                                            <li>Respect driver</li>
                                            <li>Follow safety instructions</li>
                                            <li>For any child carrying/riding with them </li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>4.3 Prohibited Actions</h3>
                                    <ul>
                                            <li>No illegal items</li>
                                            <li>No harassment or abuse</li>
                                            <li>No damage to vehicle</li>
                                        </ul>

                                        <h3>4.4 Cancellation</h3>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Avoid cancellations after booking</li>
                                            <li>Repeated cancellations may lead to suspension</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    <hr />
                                        <h2>5. Platform Disclaimer</h2>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>ShriGo is only a connecting platform</li>
                                            <li>Not responsible for driver/passenger behavior</li>
                                            <li>Not liable for accidents,injuries,damages or delays</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    <hr />
                                        <h2>6. Safety</h2>
                                        <p>All users must ensure safe conduct during trips.</p>
                                        <p>Both drivers and passengers share responsibility for safe conduct </p>
                                    <hr />
                                        <h2>7. Accidents & Incidents</h2>
                                        <p>Drivers and their insurance are responsible for any accidents.</p>
                                        <p>Drivers/Passengers should contact local authorities in emergencies</p>
                                    <hr />
                                        
                                        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
                                        <p>
                                            Email: shrigopb@gmail.com<br>
                                            Website: <a href="https://shrigo.in">https://shrigo.in</a>
                                        </p>

                                        <!-- ✅ ACCEPTANCE SECTION -->
                                        <div class="checkbox-section">
                                            <input type="checkbox" id="acceptTerms">
                                            <label for="acceptTerms">
                                                I have read and agree to the Terms & Conditions and Privacy Policy
                                            </label>
                                            <br>
                                            <button class="accept-btn" id="acceptBtn" disabled>Accept & Continue</button>
                                        </div>

                                        <footer>
                                            © 2026 ShriGo. All rights reserved.
                                        </footer>

                                    </div>

                                    <script>
                                                                            const checkbox = document.getElementById('acceptTerms');
                                                                            const button = document.getElementById('acceptBtn');

                                                                            checkbox.addEventListener('change', function () {
                                                                              button.disabled = !this.checked;
                                                                            });

                                                                            button.addEventListener('click', function () {
                                                                              alert("Terms accepted. You can now continue.");
                                                                              // 👉 Replace this with real backend/API call
                                                                            });
                                    </script>

               
